<%# FB-132 (2026-05-21). Turbo Frame wrap. The `<turbo-frame id="sessions_panel">`
    is rendered UNCONDITIONALLY (empty-state branch included) so a sort
    click that lands on a non-empty server-side relation can still
    replace the frame contents ‚Äî and so the empty-state itself sits
    inside the frame, ready to be replaced when sessions come back.
    Sort links emit `data-turbo-frame="sessions_panel"` (see
    `sort_link_to(frame:)` in `application_helper.rb`); on click Turbo
    fetches `/settings?sessions_sort=‚Ä¶&sessions_dir=‚Ä¶`, finds the
    matching `<turbo-frame id="sessions_panel">` in the response, and
    swaps just that subtree ‚Äî keeping notifications + stack panel
    untouched and preserving scroll + focus position. %>
<turbo-frame id="<%= frame %>" data-controller="sessions-scramble">
<% if sessions.any? %>
  <%# Beta 4 ‚Äî FB-14 (2026-05-20): the bulk-revoke `[revoke]` action
      no longer renders on its own row above the table. Instead it
      lives INSIDE the `<thead>` row, replacing the column labels
      when at least one row is selected. The column-1 select-all
      checkbox stays put.

      Beta 4 ‚Äî FB-116 (2026-05-20): swapped the header from a single
      colspan-spanning cell with inline spans (which broke column‚Üí
      data alignment per FB-108) to TWO co-existing `<tr>` rows in
      `<thead>` ‚Äî `defaultHeader` (per-column `<th>` cells matching
      the body grid) and `actionHeader` (checkbox + colspan action
      bar). The Stimulus controller flips the `hidden` attribute on
      whichever row is inactive. Per-column headers now align over
      their body columns. %>

  <%# Beta 4 ‚Äî Phase F3-DEEP-B (2026-05-20):
      Migrated to the canonical `.tui-table` styling family that ships
      with `Tui::TableComponent` (F2 primitive). Approach B ‚Äî class
      swap on the existing markup, no component refactor ‚Äî keeps the
      bulk-revoke + checkbox + chip + sortable-header logic intact
      while inheriting the TUI table grammar (hairline rows, muted
      lowercase headers, no zebra, no hover).

      Beta 4 ‚Äî FB-50 (2026-05-20): column rework. Previous columns
      were checkbox / user-agent / pinged (3 cols). New layout is
      checkbox / device / browser / ip / last seen / created (6 cols).
      The raw `user_agent` string is projected via
      `Pito::Formatter::UserAgent.device(...)` + `.browser(...)` to a
      small enumerated set. The IP `TooltipBadgeComponent` is gone ‚Äî
      it's a plain cell now. "pinged" renamed to "last seen". A new
      "created" column shows session-creation relative time.

      Beta 4 ‚Äî Phase F3-C (2026-05-20):
        * Row + header checkboxes use `Tui::CheckboxComponent` form
          mode. The stimulus targets + `data-current` host element
          live on the enclosing `<span class="sessions-table__checkbox">`
          wrapper.
        * The current-session marker uses `Tui::ChipComponent
          variant: :current` per ADR 0016 and sits in the device
          column for visibility.

      Sortable headers drive `?sessions_sort=<key>&sessions_dir=
      <asc|desc>` on `/settings` itself. %>
  <%# FB-131 (2026-05-21) ‚Äî `<colgroup>` + `table-layout: fixed` locks
      column widths so the header row swap (defaultHeader ‚Üî actionHeader)
      no longer reflows on selection.
      2026-05-24 ‚Äî inline `style="width: X%"` replaced with per-column
      classes that resolve to pixel widths in the .sessions-table CSS
      block. IP is the only flex column (`width: auto`); the rest are
      pinned because their content is bounded and predictable
      (checkbox glyph, "android"/"linux", "chrome"/"safari", "~12mo
      ago"). %>
  <table class="tui-table sessions-table">
    <colgroup>
      <col class="sessions-table__width-action">
      <col class="sessions-table__width-device">
      <col class="sessions-table__width-browser">
      <col class="sessions-table__width-ip">
      <col class="sessions-table__width-last-seen">
      <col class="sessions-table__width-created">
    </colgroup>
    <thead>
      <%# FB-116 ‚Äî Default header: per-column `<th>` cells, matching the
          body's column grid one-to-one so labels sit directly above
          their data. FB-108 alignment: text columns (device/browser/
          ip) get `--left`, date columns (last seen/created) get
          `--right` (which also stamps tabular-nums). %>
      <%# FB-146 (2026-05-21) ‚Äî REMOVE `data-tui-cursor-target="row"` from
          defaultHeader. FB-144 re-added the cursor target on the header
          row to satisfy FB-140 (k from row 1 ‚Üí select-all), but the
          user reports the "extra stop" is STILL present after FB-133's
          `.blur()` fix. Forensic enumeration of the rendered DOM showed
          exactly N+1 row stops (1 defaultHeader + N body rows) ‚Äî the
          extra is the header itself. Drop the target so row nav covers
          ONLY the N body rows; FB-140 (keyboard select-all) is parked
          pending a separate UX decision (Shift-K jump, Tab into header
          via Shift-Tab from row 1's checkbox column, or a dedicated
          keybinding). actionHeader stays untargeted as before. %>
      <%# FB-PURPLE-REGRESSION (2026-05-21 ‚Üí corrected) ‚Äî `data-tui-focusable`
          was previously on the `<tr>` itself (style `:row`) so the focus tint
          painted the full header row. That caused an N+1 focus-stop bug: the
          cursor controller counted the header as stop 0, shifting every even
          body row's index by one and making the even-row cursor paint miss.
          FB-146 already removed `data-tui-cursor-target="row"` for the same
          reason (see FB-146 comment above). The `data-tui-focusable` attrs
          are now removed from the header `<tr>` entirely. The select-all
          keyboard UX is parked pending a separate decision (see FB-146). %>
      <tr data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="defaultHeader">
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--left col-action">
          <span class="sessions-table__checkbox sessions-table__checkbox--header"
                data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="headerCheckbox"
                data-action="change->sessions-bulk-revoke#toggleAll">
            <%= render(Tui::CheckboxComponent.new(name: "__select_all", value: "yes", checked: false)) %>
          </span>
        </th>
        <%# FB-132 (2026-05-21). All five data columns are sortable.
            `sort_link_to(frame:)` adds `data-turbo-frame` +
            `data-turbo-action="advance"`, so the click navigates only
            the wrapping `<turbo-frame id="sessions_panel">` (panel-
            scoped refresh) and the browser URL still advances cleanly. %>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--left sortable sessions-table__col-device">
          <%= helpers.sort_link_to("device", "device", current_sort: sessions_sort, current_dir: sessions_dir, sort_param: "sessions_sort", dir_param: "sessions_dir", frame: frame) %>
        </th>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--left sortable sessions-table__col-browser">
          <%= helpers.sort_link_to("browser", "browser", current_sort: sessions_sort, current_dir: sessions_dir, sort_param: "sessions_sort", dir_param: "sessions_dir", frame: frame) %>
        </th>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--left sortable sessions-table__col-ip">
          <%= helpers.sort_link_to("ip", "ip", current_sort: sessions_sort, current_dir: sessions_dir, sort_param: "sessions_sort", dir_param: "sessions_dir", frame: frame) %>
        </th>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--right num sortable sessions-table__col-last-seen">
          <%= helpers.sort_link_to("last seen", "last_activity", current_sort: sessions_sort, current_dir: sessions_dir, sort_param: "sessions_sort", dir_param: "sessions_dir", frame: frame) %>
        </th>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--right num sortable sessions-table__col-created">
          <%= helpers.sort_link_to("created", "created", current_sort: sessions_sort, current_dir: sessions_dir, sort_param: "sessions_sort", dir_param: "sessions_dir", frame: frame) %>
        </th>
      </tr>
      <%# FB-116 ‚Äî Action header: shown only when ‚â•1 row is selected.
          Checkbox `<th>` stays in column 1; columns 2..N collapse
          into a single `<th colspan="5">` carrying the counter +
          [revoke] link. The Stimulus controller flips `hidden` on
          whichever <tr> is inactive so only one is visible at a
          time.

          FB-131 (2026-05-21) ‚Äî Bug A: actionHeader's column-1 `<th>`
          now ALSO renders a select-all checkbox (a SECOND
          `headerCheckbox` target). Without it, the column-1 cell goes
          blank when ‚â•1 row is selected and the user has no
          deselect-all affordance. Stimulus auto-collects both as
          `headerCheckboxTargets`; the controller's `update()` syncs
          state across both inputs and `toggleAll()` reads from
          whichever was clicked. %>
      <tr data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="actionHeader" hidden>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--left col-action">
          <span class="sessions-table__checkbox sessions-table__checkbox--header"
                data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="headerCheckbox"
                data-action="change->sessions-bulk-revoke#toggleAll">
            <%= render(Tui::CheckboxComponent.new(name: "__select_all_action", value: "yes", checked: false)) %>
          </span>
        </th>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--left sessions-table__header-swap" colspan="5"
            data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="headerCell">
          <span class="sessions-table__header-actions" data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="actions">
            <span class="sessions-table__counter" data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="counter">0 selected</span>
            <a data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="link" class="bracketed-muted">[revoke]</a>
          </span>
        </th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <%# FB-165 (2026-05-21) ‚Äî body rows are now generic `[data-tui-focusable]`
          targets keyed by `row_<session_id>`. Header rows stay outside
          the focus ring (sort is `s`/`S` driven separately).

          FB-166 (2026-05-21) ‚Äî focusables come from the Ruby
          `#focusables` contract (see component class); the template
          zips the ordered list with the rendered rows and emits the
          `data-tui-focusable` + `data-tui-focusable-style` attrs from
          each entry. CSS keys off the style for per-element focus visuals. %>
      <%# FB-174 (2026-05-21) ‚Äî `focusables[0]` is `select_all`; session
          rows are at `focusables[1..]`. The `i + 1` offset reflects
          the contract change in `Sessions::TableComponent#focusables`. %>
      <% sessions.each_with_index do |s, i| %>
        <% f = focusables[i + 1] %>
        <tr class="tui-table__row"
            data-tui-focusable="<%= f[:key] %>"
            data-tui-focusable-style="<%= f[:style] %>">
          <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--left col-action">
            <span class="sessions-table__checkbox"
                  data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="checkbox"
                  data-action="change->sessions-bulk-revoke#toggle"
                  data-current="<%= current_flag(s) %>"
                  data-value="<%= s.id %>">
              <%= render(Tui::CheckboxComponent.new(name: "ids[]", value: s.id, checked: false)) %>
            </span>
          </td>
          <%# FB-132 (2026-05-21). Read `device` + `browser` straight off
              the row ‚Äî they're now real DB columns derived at write
              time by `Session#derive_device_and_browser`. The legacy
              `Pito::Formatter::UserAgent` call is the fallback for pre-
              migration rows that haven't been backfilled yet
              (operator runs `bin/rails pito:sessions:backfill_device_browser`). %>
          <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--left sessions-table__cell-device">
            <%= s.device.presence || Pito::Formatter::UserAgent.device(s.user_agent.to_s) %><% if current?(s) %> <%= render(Tui::ChipComponent.new(label: "this", variant: :current)) %><% end %>
          </td>
          <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--left sessions-table__cell-browser">
            <%= s.browser.presence || Pito::Formatter::UserAgent.browser(s.user_agent.to_s) %>
          </td>
          <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--left sessions-table__cell-ip">
            <%= Pito::Formatter::IpAddress.call(s.ip) %>
          </td>
          <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num sessions-table__cell-last-seen"><%= helpers.compact_time_ago(s.last_activity_at) %></td>
          <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num sessions-table__cell-created"><%= helpers.compact_time_ago(s.created_at) %></td>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
    </tbody>
  </table>
<% else %>
  <p class="text-muted" style="margin: 0;">no active sessions.</p>
<% end %>
</turbo-frame>
